     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="41"/>
   <head>TO MY APPROVED AND MVCH RESPECTED FRIEND, <hi>
         <gap reason="illegible: under-inked" extent="1 span">
            <desc>〈…〉</desc>
         </gap>: W▪</hi>
   </head>
   <lg>
      <l>TO thee thou more then thrice beloued friend,</l>
      <l>I too vnworthie of so great a blisse:</l>
      <l>These harsh tun'd lines I he<gap reason="illegible: missing" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>e to thee commend,</l>
      <l>Thou being cause it is now as it is:</l>
      <l>For hadst thou held thy tongue by silence might,</l>
      <l>These had bene buried in obliuions night.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>If they were pleasing, I would call them thine,</l>
      <l>And disavow my title to the verse:</l>
      <l>But being bad, I needs must call them mine,</l>
      <l>No ill thing can be clothed in thy verse.</l>
      <l>Accept them then, and where I haue offended,</l>
      <l>Rase thou it out, and let it be amended.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>S. P.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
